SIT Graduates Continue to Enjoy Strong Employment Outcomes  Amid COVID-19
95.0% of graduates employed six months after graduation
Graduates from the Singapore Institute of Technology (SIT) continue to be in demand, with high overall employment and starting salaries. The 2020 Joint Autonomous University Graduate Employment Survey (JAUGES)
1
findings
2
revealed that 95.0%
3
of SIT graduates in the labour force
4
who completed their studies between October 2019 and September 2020 were employed. This is higher than the 90.7% overall employment figure in the previous year.
A total of 1,882 or 86.6% of the university’s cohort of 2,172 graduates from SIT and its nine Overseas University (OU) partners across 39 degree programmes participated in SIT’s seventh annual GES, which was conducted between 1 March and 14 May 2021.
